entries.name: PEMCertChainLib
entries.description: Library for managing PEM certificate chains.

entries.name: ForcedInclusionStore
entries.description: Contract that allows users to enqueue forced transactions via L1. The system guarantees that at least one pending forced transaction from the queue will be processed every 255 batches. Individual transactions may face longer delays if the queue is extensive.

entries.name: TaikoL1
entries.description: Main contract implementing the logic for proposing and proving Taiko blocks on L1.

entries.name: SignerList
entries.description: A signer list for registering agents, similar to a Multisig.

entries.name: AutomataDcapV3Attestation
entries.description: Contract managing SGX attestation certificates.

entries.name: Taiko Token
entries.description: ERC20 contract implementing the TAIKO token. It defines a list of addresses designated as non-voting.

entries.name: EmergencyMultisig
entries.description: Modular Governance contract allowing for proposing, voting on and executing encrypted proposals (e.g. for Security Council emergency proposals).

proposalCount.description: The total count of encrypted emergency proposals created.

entries.name: EncryptionRegistry
entries.description: A registry for signers (of the Security Council) to appoint agents to operate on their behalf. These agents can also register their encryption keys for encrypted emergency proposal support.

entries.name: RiscZeroGroth16Verifier
entries.description: Verifier contract for RISC Zero Groth16 proofs (version 2.2.0).

entries.name: SigVerifyLib
entries.description: Library for verifying signatures.

entries.name: DefaultResolver
entries.description: Maps contract names to contract addresses. Changes in this mapping effectively act as contract upgrades.

entries.name: ProverSet
entries.description: An operator proxy used by the Taiko team for operating (proposing, proving) the based rollup from permissioned addresses.

entries.name: Risc0VerifierGateway
entries.description: Entry contract to verify batches using RISC Zero.

trustedImages.description: Image IDs (i.e. program digest) of Risc0 programs trusted by this verifier gateway. Only proofs for these programs can be successfully verified. Note that proofs contains image ID data within them.

entries.name: TaikoDAOController
entries.description: Middleware contract that maintains ownership of DAO-controlled assets and contracts. Its token weight does not count towards the DAO quorum.

entries.name: MainnetSignalService
entries.description: The SignalService contract serves as cross-chain message passing system. It defines methods for sending and verifying signals with merkle proofs.

entries.name: SgxVerifier
entries.description: Verifier contract for SGX proven blocks.

entries.name: TaikoWrapper
entries.description: Entry point for proposing blocks. It enforces the inclusion of forced transactions after their deadline.

entries.name: VerifierGateway
entries.description: Gateway contract for the multi-proof system. It redirects proof to the appropriate verifier based on the proof type.

entries.name: SP1VerifierGateway
entries.description: Entry contract to verify batches using SP1.

trustedPrograms.description: Program hashes of SP1 programs trusted by this verifier gateway. Only proofs for these programs can be successfully verified. Note that proofs contains program hash data within them.

entries.name: PreconfRouter
entries.description: Entry point for batch proposals under the pre-confirmation architecture. It allows batches to be proposed only by whitelisted addresses.

entries.name: MainnetBridge
entries.description: Shared bridge for Taiko chains for bridged ETH.

entries.name: Multisig
entries.description: Modular Governance contract allowing for proposing, voting on and executing proposals (e.g. for Security Council standard proposals).

entries.name: L1SharedAddressManager
entries.description: Maps contract names to contract addresses. Changes in this mapping effectively act as contract upgrades.

entries.name: TaikoDAOController
entries.description: Middleware contract that maintains ownership of DAO-controlled assets and contracts. Its token weight does not count towards the DAO quorum.

entries.name: PreconfWhitelist
entries.description: Contains the whitelist of addresses allowed to propose batches on L1. These operators can also issue pre-confirmation from their public addresses. Currently, there are 4 operators registered.

entries.name: SP1Verifier
entries.description: Verifier contract for SP1 proofs (v5.0.0).
